==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gelsemium
<hw>Gel*se"mium</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. It.
<ets>gelsomino</ets> jasmine.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A genus of climbing plants. The yellow (false) jasmine
(<spn>Gelsemium sempervirens</spn>) is a native of the Southern United
States. It has showy and deliciously fragrant flowers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>The root of the yellow jasmine,
used in malarial fevers, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gelt</ent>⟦br⟧
